articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel's military has warned Gaza residents that they risk being identified as accomplices "in a terrorist organisation" if they do not move south, Palestinians there said, amid growing humanitarian fears with little aid being allowed in.
articles.title: New Israeli warning to Gaza residents as first aid trickles in

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli aircraft struck two Hezbollah cells in Lebanon early on Monday, which were planning to launch anti-tank missiles and rockets toward Israel, its military said, as fighting flared across the two countries' shared border.
articles.title: Israel strikes two Hezbollah cells in Lebanon, military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel expanded planned evacuations of communities on its northern front with Lebanon on Sunday as cross-border clashes with fighters from Lebanese group Hezbollah have intensified since the war in Gaza erupted more than two weeks ago.
articles.title: Israel expands evacuations as Lebanon border clashes escalate

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli warplanes bombarded areas near three hospitals in the Gaza Strip early on Monday, Palestinian media reported, but it was not immediately clear whether the hospitals themselves suffered damage.
articles.title: Israel strikes hit areas near three Gaza hospitals, Palestinian media report

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A second convoy of aid trucks entered the Egyptian side of the Rafah border crossing on Sunday, heading towards the Gaza Strip, according to Egyptian security and humanitarian sources at Rafah.
articles.title: Second aid convoy enters Egyptian side of Rafah crossing en route to Gaza, sources say

articles.author: Andrea Shalal, Kanishka Singh
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden on Sunday ramped up his engagement with the ongoing war between Israel and the Palestinian Islamist group Hamas, convening a call with the leaders of Canada, France, Britain, Germany and Italy, after speaking with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel.
articles.title: Biden holds call with key Western allies, Pope to discuss Israel-Hamas war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of people waving Palestinian flags and chanting "Gaza, Paris is with you" gathered on Sunday for the first pro-Palestinian demonstration allowed by police in the French capital since the Oct. 7 Hamas attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Thousands join Paris's first authorised pro-Palestinian demo since Hamas attacks

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel's attacks concentrated on the Gaza Strip's centre and north, Palestinian media reported. A strike on a house near the Jabalia refugee camp, in northern Gaza, killed several Palestinians and wounded others, according to media reports.
articles.title: Israel strikes Gaza, Lebanon overnight; Netanyahu convenes generals

articles.author: Nicolás Misculin, Candelaria Grimberg, Anna-Catherine Brigida
articles.description: Massa had around 36% of the vote, ahead of Milei on just over 30%, while conservative Patricia Bullrich was behind on 23.7% with some 80% of the vote counted, a result that defied pre-election polls that had predicted a libertarian win.
articles.title: Argentina's Peronists seal election run-off with libertarian Milei

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian forces aiming to contain a four-month-old Ukrainian counteroffensive maintained unrelenting pressure on Sunday on the shattered town of Avdiivka in the east and intensified shelling in the southern area of Kherson.
articles.title: Russian forces intensify pressure on Ukraine's Avdiivka, Kherson
